narratives.question_text: What knowledge, skills, and insights did you develop by taking this course?
comments: I learned more about biomaterials and about our bodies responses to them.

narratives.question_text: What are the strengths and weaknesses of this course and how could it be improved?
comments: I think this was a really great course. I learned so much useful information that I could use in the future whether as a research scientist or someone working in industry. The lectures were really engaging and professor Gonzalez is a superb professor. My only critique is that sometimes it seemed like we went through material too fast.

narratives.question_text: Would you recommend this course to another student? Please explain.
comments: Definitely! If you have any interest in biomaterials, I think you will find this course to be really engaging. The topics are really interesting and professor Gonzalez does an amazing job keeping the material relevant to the innovation going on right now. Lastly, the work load is really manageable.
Yes, it is a blend of biology, mechanics and material science that fits perfect with biomedical engineering.
Yes it is an interesting way to learn more about materials and our bodies and wasnt terribly difficult.
